about:
I am a terribly boring nonfiction reader. I love fiction but tend to only read fiction to "recharge" between the books in my ever-growing bulky-and-boring pile.

I just had goodreads connect to my amazon.com account and retrieve all the books I've ever bought. I'm embarrassed because I will be dead long before I ever get to reading them all.

Oh well, at least I'll be able to make a nice "planned contribution" to a city library somewhere.
